description:
Before Mary Jane came Gwen Stacy - Peter Parker's first big love, which was brutally murdered by the Green Goblin. This story tells, how they both fell in love, and how Spider-Man was forced, to fight agains dangerous villains, to win the heart of the girl of his dreams.

Collects: Spider-Man: Blue #1-6
name: Vol. 25 - Spider-Man - Blue

description: AN ACT OF FAITH #9 is the second half of the two-part "The Ark" storyline. In the 1980s, there were two failed missions to find Noah's Ark. On the first mission, Professor Jack led the super-hero team, the Protectors. On the second mission, the Protectors went without Professor Jack. The second mission ended terribly. For decades, Professor Jack blamed himself for the failed missions. Now, in hopes to make amends, Professor Jack takes Nemish-Man, Crusader Girl, and Kid-Cockroach to Mount Ararat to retrieve Noah's Ark once and for all!
name: The Ark Part 3

description: With the mystery of Emily's disappearance growing deeper and darker, events take a nightmarish turn. As Hellinger navigates surreal, haunted dreamscapes, he is confronted with ghosts from his past, and chilling omens of his future. Elsewhere, enemies are revealed, and sharp implements are put to use. Features a cover by superstar artist Garry Brown (The Massive.)
name: Part Three: Follow the Fox

description: You wanted unbridled Angelica action? You're getting unbridled Angelica action! With George's mother held hostage by a rogue NSA agent, the gloves come off as Angelica faces an enemy who knows her inside and out - her creator. Will she revert to being a heartless killing machine, or has her time with George changed her forever? It's the shopping-mall-shattering conclusion!

THE UNCANNY UNICORNEA!

AW YEAH COMICS!

Beautiful Downtown Skokie has just survived the NINJA ATTACK! How will our heroes deal with the awesome might of the Uncanny Unicornea! The creature with ONE eye and ONE horn! ALSO! The threat is not over...until we get a case of FROST BITE! Then an Evil Bug attack! Oh NO! Could that be the evil MARQUAID?! This issue is action packed with all kinds of awesome! Featuring Action Cat and Adventure Bug! and...The Daring Dogs go up against an Evil Robot Monster Beast! Lots of Giants in this issue. even an appearance by ZOMBIE CAT. AW YEAH COMICS!

Using an enchanted potion Mary frees her companions from the Dream Queen's spell. But time is running out for them, they must find the talisman they've been searching for to release Mother Night and discover their true nature. As an all out assault on the palace ensues, their final confrontation between light and dark will ultimately reveal all.

Note: The digital edition (9/24/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Gotham City is once again under attack by the wife of the late Max Black – and as usual, Widow Black’s persuasive powers are hard to resist. This time she has a formidable foil…none other than the pernicious Penguin. Together, they are set to plunder the wealthy of Gotham City. Will the Dynamic Duo be caught in her deadly web of deceit?
name: Caught in the Widow's Web

description: Vigilante’s gone missing, and it’s up to Batman to track him down…that is, if the Phantasm doesn’t get to him first!
name: Mark of the Phantasm, Part 2 of 2

description: Professor Mortimer is bequeathed an old house in France by a former adversary: Miloch, the evil genius of SOS Meteors fame. Along with the house is a letter inviting the Briton, as the only man of worthy intellect, to discover a fabulous invention left behind by the departed. Following recorded instructions, Mortimer activates the device … and wakes up a hundred million years in the past! Thus begins an incredible odyssey through time…
name: The Time Trap

description:
The House of the Rising Sun

THE PENULTIMATE ISSUE. The road trip of revenge barrels closer to its final destination, taking the brothers face-to-face with a notorious Baton Rouge drug lord with nefarious ties to the James family. As the bullets and emotions fly, Tracy's hidden agenda is revealed, threatening to tear Jack and John apart for good. One thing's for sure, things will never be the same for the brothers James. If this ending doesn't kill you...you're already dead!
name: The House of the Rising Sun

description: About to be sent to a small country in Central America, Buck, Sonny and Tumb are given a special briefing by two high-ranking US government agents. Under the cover of their official mission – train Managuan Air Force pilots in the use of their brand new F-18s – the three men are to try and overfly a strangely modern airfield suspected of belonging to a drug cartel. Problem: the airfield is in the middle of a no-fly zone…
name: No-Fly Zone

description: The sun always rises, even in Nachtwald, and for Priscilla it's a brand new day full of promise. Baseball tryouts are going as well as could be hoped. There's edible food to be found, and a bewitching, broomstick-riding friend to share it with. Plus Balthazar, town prince and school idol, seems interested in dating her. There's just one problem: Kitten wanted him first! When the green-eyed monster of jealousy and a set of snobby vampire grandparents descend on Nachtwald, Priscilla might have to hop a broomstick back to America just to stay sane.
name: Vol. 2

description:
THE TENTH DOCTOR FACES EMOTIONAL ARMAGEDDON IN NEW YORK!

Torn between the homeworld of vicious psychic parasites, and the worsening chaos in Sunset Park, the Doctor must battle through his worst nightmares in order to save the lives of everyone in New York - and the world!

His sole ally, if she's strong enough to withstand the aliens' psychic predations? Gabriella Gonzalez!

With the help of a trusty Sonic Screwdriver and a frustrated Mexican-American artist, trapped in her father's Laundromat... can the Doctor defeat the ultimate bad spirits?

And what will be left of Gabby's corner of the world if she and the Doctor succeed?

Nick Abadzis and Elena Casagrande are joined by new regular cover artist Verity Glass to blow the TARDIS doors off - as Gabriella's first arc comes to a stunning conclusion!

Plus: every issue is packed with extras, including humor strips!

Note: The digital edition (9/24/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

name: Revolutions of Terror Part 3

description:
a boy and a beagle

in a wordless comic, a boy meets a beagle. a friendship develops.
name: A Boy and A Beagle

description: Six new Fez adventures in one 24-page package! Join the Man Who Isn't There as he exorcises Queen Victoria, burns a witch on a first date, and defies Death its very self!

Imagine a puzzle. A magic puzzle. It features the head of a Turk, it’s big and complicated, and when you finish assembling it, the person you think about at that moment is smashed into a thousand pieces! Now, imagine how many ways things can go wrong if Iznogoud of all people tries to use that puzzle, hmm? Sirens, shrinking potions, magic calendars… All fantastic opportunities for disasters to occur – and hilarity to ensue!
name: Iznogoud and the Jigsaw Turk

description:

BCover BRussell Dauterman1
CCover CLipeMissing

Melusine, the young witch-in-training, divides her time between studying at the sorcery school and working au pair at the local vampire’s castle. That’s a lot of pressure, and she needs some distractions and fun too. So, what better way to take your mind off things than a good old-fashioned session of story telling with your friends? Dragons, enchanters, princes and princesses all get the fairy tale treatment – except, well, Melusine’s no fairy…
name: Tales of the Full Moon

description:
Maternal Impressions

As Merrick recovers from his journey across Europe and his return to London we learn more of his origin.

As Merrick recovers from his journey across Europe and back to London, we learn more about his origins.

Treves and his friends locate a rare occult book that has caught the attention of more than just the Masons. They enlist Merrick to help them get it in exchange for help tracking down Ferrari.
name: Maternal Impressions

description: Tubbs is in hot pursuit of Sonny's kidnappers as Pasqual's men race to make their escape. The chase ends at a mansion fortress where the Organized Crime Bureau team shoots it out with the Pasqual's men. Crockett and Tubbs put their differences aside as they try to stop Pasqual's escape attempt. Crockett fights it out with Fernando as Tubbs discovers that his new love interest helped betray the team. Pasqual escapes back to his overseas employer and the team realizes that the new threat to Miami is far from over.

After a chance encounter at sea, fisherman Mishka washes ashore on an uncharted island. Surrounded by monsters and worse, can Mishka survive long enough to solve the mystery of the Sea Devil and return home?

Oops with the help of his new friend, a rat named Plague, team up to search for answers behind his mysterious family heirloom. However, Plague delights in stirring up chaos as they quest; by terrorizing the market patrons, playing practical jokes on serious knights, and breaking into a forbidden library. With the Chief of Knights constantly hot on their trail, Oops pulls out all the stops in his magical abilities to escape their clutches and find his family.

Pewfell is a slacker wizard who lives in the fabulous city of Spirekassle. He's married to Tina the Warrior Princess and is landlord to a small blue gnome who hates him.

In this episode, Pewfell finds himself trapped in the surreal Planes of Oss. Meanwhile, Tina the Warrior Princess leads an all-out aerial assult on the demon-god who threatens to destroy the whole city.

This issue concludes volume 2 of the Pewfell saga, and the "For the Love of Hornbag" story arc. It is rated 17+ for naked wizards.

Manfred Von Richthofen survived his first aerial combat with light injuries only. As a rear gunner, though, he felt particularly frustrated by his inability to control the plane. Convinced that he must be able to fly and shoot at the same time to make the most of his mysterious mind-reading ability, he works hard to obtain his pilot licence. It’s in March 1916, in the sky over Verdun, that the Red Baron earns his first victory as a pilot…
name: Rain of Blood

description: Wonder Woman: Amazon princess, merciless crimefighter, and…rock star? Share a moment with Diana as she rocks out on stage with her band and fights to protect some teenagers from a threat.
name: Bullets and Bracelets

description:
The dogs of war are gnawing at their leashes! The forces of darkness have hounded Becky Montcrief since she first placed her hand on the Sixth Gun. Now, Becky and her allies are taking the fight to their enemies. Their goal-destroy the cursed guns once and for all! But the Grey Witch has plans on her own, and she stages a shockingly brutal counter-attack! The unexpected outcome of this battle will change the fate of the Six forever! This is the beginning of the end!

This volume collects The Sixth Gun issues #36-41.
name: Book 7: Not The Bullet, But The Fall

description: ComixTribe's acclaimed superhero drama returns! The horrifying truth behind Alex Thomas' murder stands revealed. As The Standard is faced with defeat and despair, Zena Zarthos is haunted by the ghosts of her past and the difficult choices that lie in her future. Is this the beginning of the end?

Everyone is talking about Windy Island’s new surf center, even Nicky’s hero, Australian surf champion Gary Moon! The artificial reef is supposed to create perfect waves. But the Thea Sisters have discovered a dangerous secret: even a surf champion can’t face these giant waves! it’s up to them to break the story before another reef is built off the shore of their beloved Donkey Beach.

Note: The digital edition (9/24/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Catching The Giant Wave

description: With Twisted Dark Vol. 2, Neil Gibson reinforces his message that comic books are not just for kids. Through the book's pages we find familiar characters from Vol 1 and meet brand new faces as the connections between stories begin to make themselves clear.
name: Volume Two

description:
Featuring screen-capture images from MARVEL'S ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN The smash Disney XD hit webs its way right out of your TV!

Scorpio and the Zodiac have taken over the S.H.I.E.L.D. Helicarrier! Now, Spider-Man and Nick Fury must put their differences aside and team up!

Spider-Man is put on a S.H.I.E.L.D. security detail to protect J. Jonah Jameson from the Beetle, on the same day Mary Jane has an interview at the Daily Bugle!

Spidey and the team sneak off to a desert island for a vacation! But it's hard to relax when the beach beneath your feet is the villainous Sandman!

After Hulk falls sick with an alien infection caused by the Phalanx, Spider-Man, tries to hide him at his house! It's all-out action and excitement as the hit Disney XD TV show bursts off the screen and into your hands with these screen-capture adaptations! Collecting MARVEL UNIVERSE ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN #25-28.
name: Volume 7

description: Eddie continues his job search and must deal with unscrupulous business owners, unsympathetic Human Resources departments and more. Follow the adventures of the unemployed in this hilarious slice-of-life series.

The groundbreaking digital comic returns! Half a million downloads, and the inspiration for everything from Thrillbent itself to comics like Moth City! Read where it all began! Valentine is discovered miles behind French lines, with no idea how he got there. Branded a deserter, Valentine is now enemy to both his own army and to the red-eyed demons who seem to be everywhere, even in the hospital.

Every 100 years or so, the infertile people of Simlanne send their champions to the sacred island of Filene, where the best among them, chosen via a series of tests, will find and bring back the next generation. This cycle, though, the local heroes seem to fail repeatedly, and the aging Simlannians have sent for heroes from other worlds. Valerian, chosen to represent Earth, will have to overcome the tests and his competitors in a dangerous odyssey…
name: Heroes of the Equinox

description: The finale of 2014's most talked about horror comic! Can Detective Gorley finally get to the bottom of the string of grisly murders plaguing his town? Are video nasties really to blame, or is something more sinister afoot? It all ends here!
After a bumpy ride, Deron arrives in Balathar for the next step of the plan to save Cody. Can he get to him in time to prevent the annexation ceremonies? Find out in our penultimate issue!
Hunting an assassin on a pricey resort planet, Zaya finds herself in the middle of a heated firefight between competing agencies and the rampaging target himself!

Welcome To Port Drogo -or- Filling Cavities

Disgraced writer and unremitting smart-ass Owen Jelinsky is desperate to salvage his gnarled literary reputation while ducking hitmen out to deliver his demise. Hiding out in Port Drogo, a fringe city where outlandish body-modification is the norm, Owen is attempting to unearth the city's rumored illicit underground. A network of black-market surgeons drastically changing the identities of known criminals through extreme surgical means. But carving his way to Port Drogo's grizzly epicenter will mean following the questionable guidance of a shadowy mobster/con-man known only as "Gristle".
name: Welcome To Port Drogo -or- Filling Cavities

description: In 1962, in the pages of a comic book slated for cancellation, Stan Lee and Steve Ditko gave birth to one of the most enduring icons in American popular culture: the Amazing Spider-Man! Turning the concept of a super hero on its head, they imbued the young, guilt-ridden Peter Parker with the fantastic powers of an arachnid and the fantastic pressures of an everyday teenager. The combination was pure magic. Now, you can leap into Spider-Man's web-slinging world from the very beginning, including the tragic origin that started it all; the first appearances of the Daily Bugle and J. Jonah Jameson; and the debut of classic villains including the Green Goblin, Dr. Octopus, the Sandman, the Vulture and Electro! Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN (1963) #1-17 and ANNUAL #1, and material from AMAZING FANTASY (1962) #15.
name: TPB

volume.name: The Amazing Spider-Man Epic Collection: Great Power

description: OH MY GOD! Vacation plans are made! But annoying screaming ghosts, crappy goblins, and a terrible excuse for mother, may spoil it all. See if our devilishly sexy vampire, Valdu, can make it to the little town of Goblin Spelled Backwards. It's just the most darn near hospitable place around, y'all!

Collecting the first 6 issues of Blastosaurus 'Welcome to Freak Out City' tells the story of a man who really wishes he wasn't shaped like a dinosaur. Fighting evil mutant raptors, robots and trying to rescue notably unadorable children wasn't what he signed up for... Then again, he didn't sign up for any of it.
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Blastosaurus: Welcome To Freak Out City

description: Bob is a story of a boy's childhood pet dog through the eyes of the people that loved him. From Bob's first days to his last this comic details the experience of loving a pet and the effect it has on your life.

Some say he is a force of nature. Others say he is a reject of a hormone injected time gone by. The facts are, he's the most unstoppable cop on the force. This high octane splatterfest will follow BPC and his partner as they battle the notorious Fuster Cluck gang. King Bone Press will bring you a 32 page one shot comic featuring a tale of the cock with a glock.

An up-and-coming mystery writer, Michael, has a strong dislike toward women after his divorce from his former wife, which is why he refused to hire a secretary despite his busy schedule. When his old friend introduces him to Jenny, he decides to hire her on the spot. Her talent as a secretary is one reason; another reason lies in her old ring with an engraving that catches his interest. Michael visits Slinterwood, a mansion on Mirren Island, with Jenny for plotting his next novel. Little do they know the ring will bring their fates together....
name: Vol. 1

description: Adapted from the first episode of the web series "The Challenger" by Suit & Stubble Productions, join Rick Sledge as he infiltrates the seedy underbelly of Los Angeles crime families while being saddled with a new, uptight and by-the-book partner, Ronnie Gunnerson.

A disgraced outcast samurai living in early seventeenth-century Manila, Kitazume is contemplating ritual suicide when a divine force (of a sort) intervenes: Luis, a rogue Jesuit priest and Kitazume's longtime friend. At Luis's insistence, the samurai agrees to help smuggle a Manchu princess to Mexico. But little does he know that he's really been dragged into an epic struggle for power.

Several forces have their malicious sights set on the New World's rich silver mines: an insurgent Spanish duke, Chinese political interests, and the escaped African slaves known as the cimarrónes. And working in secret among them is a mysterious, long-lost order that has its own plans for the precious metal.

As politics and greed collide, Kitazume must call upon his deadly skills once more. But he's not just fighting to save his friends--he's fighting for the redemption he so desperately craves.

volume.name: Cimarronin: A Samurai In New Spain

description:
The Case of the Mysterious Zita Makara, Part 1

Los Angeles, 1940: Private investigator Dash Malone can't shake the feeling his lover, Johnny, is hiding something. Strange deaths start occurring throughout the city while a mysterious woman named Zita Makara begs Dash to take her case. When a grisly murder connects all three, a terrifying mystery unfolds.

Note: The digital edition (9/24/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: The Case of the Mysterious Zita Makara, Part 1

description:
What is best in life? Cats and the Internet, of course. And when you put the two together, you have the third collection of Rich Stevens' long-running and pioneering pixel comic, Diesel Sweeties!

Watch as the Diesel Sweeties gang explores the two oft-debated questions in life: "Why is my internet not working?" and "What does the damn cat want now?" For anyone struggling to remember the official ranking of social media (Hint: the acronym is GIFT) or wondering what it means to ship Roomba x Cat, this collection is a godsend. Or, at the very least, a "send."
name: Volume 3

volume.name: Diesel Sweeties: There Is A Cat of the Internet

description: Based off the New York Times best selling novels. The Iron King is the first book in the Iron Fey series, and follows the adventures of a girl named Meghan Chase. On her sixteenth birthday, Meghan discovers her little brother has been kidnapped by a faery race known as "the Fey" and even worse, replaced with an evil changeling and taken into the "Nevernever." Meghan bravely ventures into the faery realm to rescue him, and that's where an epic plot unfolds. This collected edition has never before images and character designs!
name: TPB

description: Blake Taska is a young and cynical junior professor. She hates her job and is terrified of her students. Her reason? One of them shot and killed her. Now, trapped in the afterlife, she is forced to work in a hellish education factory where she explores her past relationships, emotional short-comings, and the cataclysmic effects of promising a nonexistent American dream.

Sheryl Sandberg's book, Lean In, works to inform professional women how to be more successful in their professional lives while leading fulfilling, personal ones. The story behind the American businesswoman (the Chief Operating Officer of Facebook), her book, and her success is as compelling as any self-help book and as "liked" as any post.

Hollywood Nights

Violet is a young woman with unusual abilities. On this night, she has her rival at her mercy. With great power comes great drama.
name: Hollywood Nights

description:
'The White Box'

The assassination of a president, the experiments of a secret government organization, betrayal, redemption, loss and regret, corruption, guns and fists, brotherly love and a seven foot tall hero with a gravity-defying vertical and fists as hard as diamonds--Garcia Brothers has it all.
name: The White Box

description: The Ghoul Squad matches wits with a werewolf!

Featuring the all new cast of Grimm Fairy Tales! When Sela and Belinda are out on a mission, Skye and the students sneak out on Halloween night to visit a haunted cemetery. But when a wraith attacks and brings each of their greatest fears to life, the heroes of the story are made into prey!

Aftermath

"Left to die... alone. Or so I thought..."

Thenn has spent 5 years fighting the tyrannical Chears, only to be mutinied by the crew she trusted, and left for dead on a trash-dump of a planet. Without food or water, Thenn has no hope to survive, and knows she will die-forgotten and alone.

But she is not as alone as she believes...
name: Aftermath

description: After a satisfying meal of pizza and a 40oz, Natalie and her girlfriend Emily are visited by an unannounced guest - the Holy Spirit! What plans could God possibly have for the two? A talking slice of pizza, a powerful evil, and divine intervention in the first issue of this 3 issue mini-series!

"A husband by arrangement, no way!" Maddy has been forced by her grandfather to marry Dexter Fitzgerald, the heir of a prominent family in Portugal. Little does her grandfather know, she has a plan of her own! If she trades her innocent nature for one of a party girl and acts like a gold digger, there is no way Dex will want her then...right? But what happens when Dexter's reaction is the exact opposite of what she expects? The new Maddy seems to be just his type!
name: Vol. 1

description: Upon hearing news of her father's death, Laura returns to her hometown in Wales for the first time in over ten years.Waiting for her there is her older stepbrother, Oliver, with whom she once shared a forbidden love. "And I told myself that I would never make the same mistake again...." Laura is troubled by her realization that, even now, her love for him has not been extinguished. But Laura is unaware of the role that her stepmother, Stella, played in their separation and in her father's death!
name: Vol. 1

description: Redcoats-ish, Jeff Martin's War of 1812 collects the complete 101 comic strip run of a weekly web-comic featuring the misadventures of John and George, two not so fearless men of the Canadian militia. Heeding the call to defend Canada against the invading American army, John and George are now doing their best to be heroes, whilst also working hard to avoid battles, marching, danger or anything else that involves effort. This a good fun read for anyone looking for War of 1812 adventures that make you chuckle.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Dance 1

Five superhuman women are sent to a secret facility in a nondescript location to eliminate a target and retrieve data. Nothing but intentionally vague details are given, but all of the women follow their orders without a second thought. All except for one, the youngest of the group: Jenna, codenamed Jet Dancer. While she obeys her commands and performs well, her mind is filled with doubt every step of the way. Are they nothing more than tools? Why are they causing this destruction? And why is Jet Dancer the only one bothered by it?
name: Dance 1

description:
Johnny Boo zooms to the moon on a star-powered skateboard, where he meets a spunky little girl ghost named Susie Boom. She has BOOM power, which is pretty darn loud. Luckily, the moon has ice cream. But oh no! It also has an ice cream monster, just like back on Earth. This book fulfills the dreams of many of our young readers, who said they wanted Johnny Boo to visit the moon. And many others who wanted to see Johnny Boo ride a skateboard. They will all be delighted by this very silly adventure.

Note: The digital edition (9/24/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Volume 6

volume.name: Johnny Boo: Zooms To the Moon

description:
Sinking in the Tar.

You'll dig the bone Rattling origin of Johnnysaurus Rex. Sink into the tar pit, as Johnny discovers new dark and sticky secrets. Can he survive a museum full of mish-mashed amalgams, running amok?!?
name: Sinking In the Tar.

description:
Totally Billy Bad Ass Bigass Super Duper Summer Special

After his finishing move killed a man in the ring, former professional wrestler Billy Badass puts his mustache and suplexing skills to use hunting down small town bounties, picking up chicks and just plain getting by any way he can. Like a Badass.

Collects Erik Lundy's Billy Badass stories plus some fun extras.
name: Totally Billy Bad Ass Bigass Super Duper Summer Special

description:
Just another day at school for these kids, that is until a creepy and glowing sphere is sent to one of them for mysterious reasons and once out of the box, it shoots beams of light everywhere...

In the blink of an eye, five regular teens find themselves lost in a completely new world where magic, airships and dangerous adventures are everywhere!

It is up to them to find the mythical city of Samarkand and hope it will bring them back home!

Collecting "Lost Kids: Seeking Samarkand" #1-8 -- written by Felipe Cagno, illustrated by Ben & Joey Vazquez, Rafael De Latorre, Ivan Anaya, Wilton Santos and more, colored by Clonerh Kimura, Everardo Orozco, Eddy Swan and packed with special guests like Artgerm, Genzoman, Loish, René Córdova, Todd Nauck and tons of other exclusive pin-ups!
name: Vol. 1

description:
In the year 2076, the fate of humanity rests in the hands of fourteen young warriors known as The Love Punks. When a rocket booster crashes into their community branded with a mysterious petroglyph, its discovery leads the Love Punks on an epic journey across the cosmos, complete with spy bots, pranks and magic crystals.

The characters are all based on the indigenous Australian kids who collaborated on the story and the digital coloring.
name: Book One: Space Junk

description:
The Killing Frost

Frantic first issue of Nightwasp. The series is a satire of superheros in print, film and on TV.
name: The Killing Frost

volume.name: Nightwasp: The Man Who Is Hardly Ever Afraid

description:
Alexis Quinn and his team of discarded superhumans take dangerous technology out of the hands of killers and redistribute it where it will save lives instead of ending them.

ORPHANS is superhumans versus the military-industrial complex.
name: TPB

description: The war in Oz against the Nome King has ended but that doesn't mean peace will immediately follow. Can the Freedom Fighters lead the way against a new evil that is consuming the magical land of OZ? Continuing the saga of Baum's classic Wonderful Wizard of Oz tales with a decidedly modern twist. Collects issues 16-20 of Oz comic series.
name: Book 4

description:
At long last I've dusted off the boxes in my basement, sifted through water-damaged college comics and even included some quality NEVER BEFORE PUBLISHED tales of satire and horror from Paranoid Tales of Neurosis. Yes, you'll see our society's foibles in black and white, documented in stories and strips, then filtered through the most cynical, angry lens possible.

TRAVEL! to a time when people did "bots" and Pearl Jam was still cool!

REVISIT! the terrible 80′s, where everyone made 'zines instead of blogs!

GAPE! as Joe "Casual" gets job after thankless job!

SEE! Video producers turn into bat-winged harpies!

SCOFF! at monkey-faced store clerks!

REVILE! the antics of a man who just cannot stand Pink Floyd!

SNEER! at the ramblings of power-tripping maniac!

WITNESS! a school where clowns are turned into fast-food hucksters!

GIGGLE! at home improvement for serial killers!

VOMIT! as body parts are severed and arterial spray gushes on innocent bystanders!

It's all here...! Superheroes that don't know right from wrong! Businessmen who think it's cool to speak loudly in a crowded room about a woman's tits! Rock promoters exposing Hollywood douchebags, thrash metal, Faces of Death, Gilligan's sex life, exploitation director Phil Cohen's latest travesty, commercials, murder, drug abuse, bondage, chickens attacking people, compact discs, gas station immolation and yes, SATAN himself... They all make an appearance in... Paranoid Tales of Neurosis: a demented rollercoaster of bad decisions, braindead zombies and terrible consequences. Get 112 pages of satirical madness for the ID in all of us, a place where EVERYONE is out to GET ME... I mean YOU!

volume.name: Paranoid Tales of Neurosis: The Comix Anthology

description: The series will focus on the fast firing, quick-witted, vengeful son of a gun known as Patch Hawkins as he courageously fends off the attacks of the savage Khareeshians; a beastly race of conquerors who have set their sights on the violent extinction of the human race.

Keillen, a boy with immense power at his side and a disregard for subtlety ventures deep into the night, prepared to fend off any that would bring harm to the innocent. With self-proclaimed justification, he plans to become the world's next great superhero!

After picking up on a police call asking for officers to investigate nearby docks, he blasts off hoping to be first at the scene. When Keillen arrives he quickly realizes that he may have just followed the call that could destroy everything he had ever hoped to be.

Newly departed on her journey to Grandma's house, Red encounters the Wolfe praying deep in the woods. Her trespass onto his private sacred moment does not go unnoticed, and the Wolfe pursues Red, much to her chagrin.
name: Red and the Wolfe

description: As death threatens every person he cares about in the world, Robin must push himself past his absolute limits to rescue them all. Does the young rogue have what it takes to save everybody or will someone's life fall through the cracks? Special cover by "Fantasic Four" artist Mario Guevara.
name: TPB

description: Classics comic monsters come realistically to life in this humorous "Alphabetory" documentary book by Chris and Elizabeth Wisnia.
A satirical comic about the icons of pop-culture Christmas doing battle as superheroes and villains, by Bill Corbett of Mystery Science Theater 3000 / RiffTrax!

Ed and Rob, thugs for hire, deal with the stresses of being a nobody in a city full of somebodies. Can they make a decent living in a world that hates them, or are they doomed to a life of petty crime, jail and, possibly, death by disintegration?

A satire on the superhero genre, Thug aims to be a four issue miniseries that offers a unique spin on a familiar comics world.

Prologue

Issue Zero of the Historical Fantasy Epic by Brian William Donnelly and Graeme Howard. In this not-to-miss Prologue issue, the stage is set. Don't miss it!

In the grand crucible of war, two great countries will learn that nations too can have souls.

And that they can be lost....
name: Prologue

description: James Douglas is a high school senior with little to show for his 17 years and no clear future ahead. Frustrated with the world around him, James finds the only way change will come is if he makes it happen. But what do his bizarre, recurring dreams portend? "The Utopian" collects all 109 pages of Pj Perez's original webcomic series, and includes full author annotations for every page of the story, offering never-before-seen insight into the process of its creation!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Aric of Dacia, a fifth century Visigoth warrior abducted and enslaved by the brutal Spider Aliens, fights his way free of his captors and steals their ultimate weapon, the X-O Manowar armor. But 1,600 years have passed while the Spider Aliens held Aric captive and the time hereturns to is not his own. Trapped in the modern day, Aric is now the last of his people, a savage warrior out of time in a world of corporate treachery and casual deceit. But, armed with the power of the X-O Manowar armor, Aric will rule... and he will make the Spider Aliens pay.

Start reading the debut adventures of Valiant's original armored hero right here, featuring work from visionary creators Bob Layton (Iron Man), Barry Windsor-Smith (Wolverine: Weapon X), Joe Quesada (Daredevil, Amazing Spider-Man), and many more. Collecting X-O MANOWAR (1992) #0 and X-O MANOWAR (1992) #1-6.

Note: The digital edition (9/24/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Valiant Masters X-O Manowar: Into the Fire

description:
Billionaire business-man and philanthropist, Alan McLean, is brutally murdered while in the comfort of his own home. Homicide detectives Janet Harvey and Marshal Daniels are assigned to the case. The situation immediately takes a bizarre turn when a neighbour claims to have seen the Grim Reaper in Alan McLean's yard on the eve of the murder.

With each passing night, as the snow falls heavily on the city, more of the wealthy elite are assassinated by the merciless Grim Reaper killer. Anyone foolish enough to interfere with the killers mission is slaughtered without prejudice. Harvey and Daniels, with little evidence, no obvious connection and a rising murder count, desperately search for clues that might reveal the identity of the masked executioner.

As the detectives move closer to solving the mystery, and capturing the Winter City Reaper, the line between good and evil, heaven and hell, truth and justice becomes increasingly blurred. Which is more sinister and disturbing: the Grim Reaper killer or the cruel and greedy world that created him?
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Winter City: Every Sin Has A Price

description: Nigel Grant has a gift: he’s very, very good at finding whatever people want for them. Thanks to that almost supernatural skill, he lives a comfortable, carefree life in London. But one day, a client and friend of his throws himself under an underground train. Shocked by the unexpected death, Nigel is soon swept into a web of intrigue, deception and death as he realises that suicide and the subsequent incidents all revolve around one person: him.
name: Nigel

description: Some people would like to have a new life, but they'd rather not have to die to get it! The recently dead are walking the dark streets of Gotham City, and Batgirl must journey to the Deco canyons of Arcadia to find who's responsible for these creepy reanimations. But Arcadia's spectral avenger, Ghost, is also hot on the trail of the zombie maker, one Malcolm Graymater, and Batgirl had better not get in Ghost's way! And when the murderous Two-Face gets in on the act to reclaim several of his reanimated henchmen, a deadly four-corner showdown headlines the fight card! Collecting the hit four-issue series. Co-published with DC Comics.
name: TPB
